t for encoding and decoding External Data Representation (XDR) data structures within the Apache Kerby project. It supplies XDR primitive and structured types plus stream utilities used by Kerby components that need interoperable binary serialization.\",\n./metadata/org.apache.kerby/kerby-xdr/index.json:26:    \"description\" : \"Apache Kerby Kerby XDR provides Java support for encoding and decoding External Data Representation (XDR) data structures within the Apache Kerby project. It supplies XDR primitive and structured types plus stream utilities used by Kerby components that need interoperable binary serialization.\",\n./forge/utility_scripts/metrics_writer.py:107:    \"\"\"Normalize a stats snapshot loaded from exploded stats files for metrics serialization.\"\"\"\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/dynamic-access-iteration.md:37:- Do not use this dynamic-class-loading pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata; those tests must still run under Native Image.\n./forge/prompt_templates/dynamic_access/optimistic-dynamic-access-iteration.md:33:- Do not use this dynamic-class-loading pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata; those tests must still run under Native Image.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:297:                  \"serialization\": [\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/test/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/MetadataFilesCheckerTaskTests.java:327:                  \"serialization\": [\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/basic_after_success.md:11:- Use only the library’s public API, no direct reflection or serialization.\n./forge/prompt_templates/after-successful-iteration/codex_after_success.md:13:- Use only the library's public API, no direct reflection or serialization.\n./forge/prompt_templates/initial/basic_initial.md:10:- Use only th