C.md:139:**3. `<groupId>/<artifactId>/<metadata-version>/reachability-metadata.json`** — the only file the plugin loads at native-image time. Schema [reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json](../metadata/schemas/reachability-metadata-schema-v1.2.0.json) (a vendored copy of the upstream GraalVM schema), with top-level keys `reflection`, `jni`, `resources`, `bundles`, `serialization`, and `foreignCalls`. Every entry must carry a `condition.typeReachable` clause (FR-M-2) so the plugin can rely on conditional registration. The legacy split-config layout (`reflect-config.json`, `jni-config.json`, …) is no longer present.\n./metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.0.GA/reachability-metadata.json:97:  \"serialization\" : [\n./metadata/org.jboss.logmanager/jboss-logmanager/1.2.1.GA/reachability-metadata.json:119:  \"serialization\" : [\n./metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpclient/4.5.14/reachability-metadata.json:30:  \"serialization\": [\n./metadata/org.apache.httpcomponents/httpclient/4.5.5/reachability-metadata.json:41:  \"serialization\": [\n./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:9:    \"description\" : \"Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\n./metadata/io.jsonwebtoken/jjwt-gson/index.json:29:    \"description\" : \"Provides Gson-based JSON serialization and deserialization support for the JJWT library. When present on the runtime classpath, it lets JJWT automatically use Gson to process JWT headers and claims.\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:5:    \"source-code-url\" : \"https://repo1.maven.org/maven2/org/jetbrains/kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/1.9.0/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm-1.9.0-sources.jar\",\n./metadata/org.jetbrains.kotlinx/kotlinx-serialization-core-jvm/index.json:6:    \"repository-url\" : \"https://github.com/Kotli