[thinking] 
[thinking] I think the approach here involves removing the top-level fake sun.misc.Cleaner and adjusting the DirectByteBufferPoolTest not to reference classOf. Class.forName might fail, but the test can still release the buffer successfully. However, dynamic coverage for DirectByteBufferPool won't include Method.invoke lines, and if the fake class and assertion are removed, the test could pass. While the developer suggests not broadening the patch, I wonder if we could find a way to exclude it without affecting other coverage.
[thinking] 
