[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating class references for tests**\n\nI think the approach here involves removing the top-level fake sun.misc.Cleaner and adjusting the DirectByteBufferPoolTest not to reference classOf. Class.forName might fail, but the test can still release the buffer successfully. However, dynamic coverage for DirectByteBufferPool won't include Method.invoke lines, and if the fake class and assertion are removed, the test could pass. While the developer suggests not broadening the patch, I wonder if we could find a way to exclude it without affecting other coverage.\n\n**Examining class loading behavior**\n\nI'm considering whether the JVM can still load a class when DirectByteBufferPool uses Class.forName. If test compilation places classes on the classpath, calling Class.forName(\"sun.misc.Cleaner\") might fail due to package sealing. The error in the stack occurs at the `classOf[sun.misc.Cleaner]` line in the Direct test, not within Gradle. I see that DirectByteBufferPoolTest fails with a NoClassDefFoundError at line 25, which is puzzling. It seems like there's a deeper issue to explore.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_076af53f5326b6eb0169fb26a818a4819fb3ca4af3fabfe33b\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-yay6S96Jt3QAeLru9eafw19AZeumT5UTgoQz9uWssiHhjA8EeHuC2HEgEM0eemqVpB56TT2a1KL9_WFWRkGEhTkgn-WznN0akNhptMHugevhZhJWOxgLUV2vFJ0zg4pazPIRlMPZm-qPQI7sOeQMEPVmEyjFw298DYu1svKk5THr9VXS0SnjRnFG3p73PLyd-cXVJCO0iOmD70PbgPKUCdOYGofReR4k4LVdocbaik5AjeHDGkiaboh87rPq-vagrKUsq-8r5G6MtEAfaelKhtAvZPPYHLMdHuPIqiF9mtg1ydG6aMXBRiOvVUPx-iA4MVCn_u40AJqH78gcQipDssXEnCaqcRb8FHxqbYzlKy2Pws3gCWnuCZJraUb1aIRFRDXwClzF57aNml4EprhrlkN6ARi4-956NHVAF8edNyTyFJT2UI7IP7vo3Cw0LGcEB1OTjOrNOrKXdzH6zHT3KV38WAxlP-TtWMB2rh1Xa10EvXwhnBsI0j8uhwW7Z9wflQSH4VSMHcUpjOLX2tT9lDwkqSs9zMuu-weEkSiGezmvQrLbnG8nRA-RTqo3Tyu7Ou4IoSLMoF9gTFZc8mjmFpCMaE1LrvCNAJJXAWlSfwCY0JeiC21ZtGN3JJ1Zu07ezTYTJ